roducts and old Forums archive<\/p>\n","icon":"fa-archive","bgColor":"#bfec76","color":"#ffffff","slug":"10/archive","parentCid":0,"topic_count":0,"post_count":0,"disabled":0,"order":7,"link":"","numRecentReplies":1,"class":"col-md-3 col-xs-6","imageClass":"cover","undefined":0,"subCategoriesPerPage":10,"minTags":0,"maxTags":5,"postQueue":1,"isSection":0,"totalPostCount":0,"totalTopicCount":0,"tagWhitelist":[],"unread-class":""},"posts":[{"pid":127445,"timestamp":1504903827000,"content":"<p dir=\"auto\">If anybody is here looking for information about what happened to Opera Coast because Opera didn't post any news about it, here it is: <strong>Coast has been discontinued<\/strong> according to some ex-employees/business contacts/friends(?) on Reddit.<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/user/kaysb\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow ugc\">kaysb<\/a>: Opera removed of most of the developers positions in the Oslo office last year, and with that, killed development of things like Coast.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/user/gsnedders\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow ugc\">gsnedders<\/a>: AFAIK, most of the people heavily involved in Coast left long before that, and there was some small skeleton team left. But I could be wrong, it's been a long time since I've spoken to anyone who was much around it.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<\/blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/user/demonstro\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow ugc\">demonstro<\/a>: Currently working with one of the designers. They're all out. An Android build was just around the corner, but now it will never happen.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<\/blockquote>\n<\/blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/user/kaysb\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow ugc\">kaysb<\/a> That could be. My memory of that period is already a bit foggy 🙂<br />\nI quit my job at Opera 5 days before the rest of my team (Core Services and Operation, or what ever the name was at the end) was told they would shut down the development in Oslo.<br />\nI did have a veeery small part of Coast; I designed, implemented and maintained the server side of Coast Card, the bookmark sharing built into Coast.<br />\nI hope the rest of the company is still doing great, but I must say that it is a bit of an eye opener to see the company from outside. Or, to be more precise, not see the company at all, even as a interested hard core user. After they removed the first-run page informing about the latest changes etc. there is very little that engages users in the product.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<\/blockquote>\n<\/blockquote>\n","timestampISO":"2017-09-08T20:50:27.000Z","user":{"uid":683,"username":"rafaelluik","userslug":"rafaelluik","picture":"/assets/uploads/profile/683-profileavatar.png","displayname":"rafaelluik","icon:text":"R","icon:bgColor":"#009688"},"index":10,"cid":31,"topic":{"slug":"22039/opera-coast-no-longer-in-app-store","title":"Opera Coast no longer in App Store?"}}]},{"cid":32,"name":"Opera Max","description":"Talk about our data management and privacy app here","descriptionParsed":"<p>Talk about our data management and privacy app here<\/p>\n","icon":"fa-opera","bgColor":"#ff1b2e","color":"#ffffff","slug":"32/opera-max","parentCid":10,"topic_count":95,"post_count":312,"disabled":0,"order":32,"link":"","numRecentReplies":1,"class":"col-md-3 col-xs-6","imageClass":"cover","subCategoriesPerPage":10,"minTags":0,"maxTags":5,"postQueue":1,"isSection":0,"totalPostCount":312,"totalTopicCount":95,"tagWhitelist":[],"unread-class":"unread","parent":{"cid":10,"name":"Archive","description":"Discussions about discontinued products and old Forums archive","descriptionParsed":"<p>Discussions about discontinued products and old Fo